A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing the week of February 10 to 14, 2025, as National FCCLA Week; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Family, Career and Community Leaders of America (FCCLA), the national
4 nonprofit, family-focused, intracurricular student organization for Family and Consumer
5 Sciences students through grade 12, helps youth assume their roles in society through Family
6 and Consumer Sciences Education in the areas of personal growth, family life, college
7 readiness, career exploration, leadership, and community involvement; and
8 WHEREAS, the organization extends classroom learning through chapter service projects
9 that develop leadership and employability skills and helps young men and women learn how
10 to plan, make decisions, carry out program evaluations, and take action through working with
11 other youth and adults within their school, community, and state; and
12 WHEREAS, FCCLA offers members an opportunity to work together for everyday purposes
13 for the improvement of themselves as well as their families, careers, and communities; and
14 WHEREAS, the week of February 10 to 14, 2025, has been designated National FCCLA
15 Week.
